          "name": "What is Answer Engine Optimization (AEO)?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Answer Engine Optimization (AEO) is a strategic approach focused on optimising digital content and architecture for answer engines and AI environments. It involves designing conversational content, implementing structured data, managing the customer journey and aligning cross‑functional teams to accelerate sales and establish category authority.\n\n- Structured data & conversational content: AEO uses JSON‑LD and question‑answer flows to make content machine‑readable and align with buyer questions.\n- Full‑funnel authority: It manages the entire customer journey, reducing friction and compressing sales cycles.\n- Cross‑functional collaboration: Marketing, sales and technical teams work together to design answer ecosystems and measure impact.\n- Measurable business outcomes: Success is defined by AI visibility, answer gap closure and revenue acceleration rather than keyword rankings.\n\nBy aligning content, data and organisational processes, AEO establishes defensible category authority and accelerates revenue growth."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How does AEO differ from traditional SEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "While traditional SEO focuses on generating traffic and improving keyword rankings, AEO shifts the emphasis to AI visibility and answer ecosystem design. It aligns content with buyer questions and measures success through revenue impact rather than raw traffic alone.\n\n- AI‑first focus: AEO optimizes structured content for answer engines and conversational AI, not just search algorithms.\n- Structured & conversational content: Uses JSON‑LD and question–answer flows instead of relying solely on keyword‑optimized blog posts.\n- Revenue metrics: Success is measured by pipeline velocity and sales cycle compression rather than traffic volumes.\n- Cross‑functional alignment: Requires collaboration between marketing, sales and technical teams to design cohesive answer ecosystems.\n- Category authority: Builds defensible authority by addressing real buyer questions and establishing topical leadership.\n\nTogether, these elements make AEO more strategic and outcome‑oriented than traditional SEO."
          }
